race.comment: Another wide open race with plenty of win chances. JESSUP (3) stalked the pace and ran on hard to score a determined win last time. Drawn for a similar run here and can make it back to back wins. GOBLINS (4) returns from a break on the back of a jump-out win and has won when fresh. Drawn to be prominent and expected to give a sight. NORDIC (5) has been freshened since starting favourite last time but settling too far back and never threatening. Rates highly on best form and worth another chance. HUSTLE (12) resumed from a long break with a solid on speed second beaten just a neck. Fitter and is a second-up winner. Among the main hopes. RUSSIAN FRONT (6) was a close-up fifth at last run and given a fresh-up since. Has switched yards and is hard to beat on best figures.
